name: All Seeing I #17
description: In VR our visual organs (eyes) see one object or one surrounding area, but brain cells perceive and react to that differently. This leads to the confusion of consciousness and the brain, in general. I have conversations with machines. The GAN was trained on the paintings of old masters. It is full of prejudices and preconceived ideas, like us. This series looks at the ecstasies of VR.
